HEADWORD: Minos
<hw>Mi"nos</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>A king and lawgiver of Crete, fabled to
be the son of <persfn>Jupiter</persfn> and <persfn>Europa</persfn>.
After death he was made a judge in the Lower Regions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

